  "script": "The animal that kills the most people in Africa is not the lion or the crocodile, it is this. The hippo. They look slow and lazy, but a hippo can run over twenty miles an hour, faster than most people can sprint, and their jaws open four feet wide with enough force to snap a canoe in half. They are fiercely territorial in the water and will capsize boats without warning. Hippos kill an estimated five hundred people a year, more than sharks, lions, and elephants combined. Behind that goofy face is Africa's deadliest heavyweight. So why does nobody warn you about them?",
